  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving milk quality and dairy product quality</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;1. Follow up on Livestock Farmer Field Schools on good farming practices&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Milk quality control&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. Insemination&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. Conduct audit of 2019&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. Aflatoxin Kit&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;6. Process to get S-Mark for Milk and Maize products&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;IAKIB is a dairy cooperative that has significantly grown in membership since 2016 and has been building up capital to participate in a dairy processing business. Due to various influences  multiple initiatives have not reached the stage of implementation and therefore IAKIB decided to start its own small scale processing facility last year. The joint venture plans have not disappeared and one may still see the cooperative become part of such a venture in the future  but for now the focus of the project with Agriterra is on improving milk quality and dairy product quality. Through FFS activities  the development of an improved milk quality control system and an intensified focus on insemination and aflatoxin control  the cooperative aims to professionalize at its foundation. Simultaneously  the processing business requires special attention  to ensure that the products made comply with Rwandan regulations in terms of quality.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;The main goals are to improve milk quality and dairy product quality  to professionalize the cooperative business further.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
